If it happens to you for the first time, in the best case you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn't matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called talking in sleep.
It is quite widespread, especially among children and young people.
Certainly, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, as during the high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason to cause this phenomenon.
Often, relationships with other phenomena are sought in sleep, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (bedding nostrils at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason to do so.
As we have already mentioned, it can be due to very high fibre, stress or over-requirements.
In any case, this is a little bit of a researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be that one speaks quietly in single words, whispers or it can be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to monitor the child and consult with a specialist to check whether there is a problem that causes fear and thus results in it.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with the sleep apnoea or with stress).
What you can do is take a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before sleeping.
So, pick a quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV programs that are terrible and a bit too wild.
For the nervous children to whom relaxation is recommended, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner peace.
It helps the child to sleep quietly.
