Thus, "hybrid" PDF-files can now be generated, which extend the typical graphics of Adobe format to the elements of a table and a text-processing system.
The cooperation is one of the most improved elements of the applications: Tables can now be worked out by several users, avoiding conflicts in the event of changes; in the case of the word processing system, each editor is assigned a Frabe to guarantee a better correction procedure.
Some companies are about to publish various functions of OpenOffice on the Internet (on the cloud), while in the coming weeks the definitive result is to be made public.
